audit_report:
The given C++ code for the function `aspath_put` is vulnerable. The vulnerability is related to a denial-of-service (DoS) issue, where an attacker can cause a session drop by constructing an invalid message due to incorrect AS_PATH size calculation. The assumption that many things tested will never happen is not a valid security measure.

The vulnerability is described in CVE-2017-16227 with a CWE-ID of CWE-20.

The code does not handle the case where the length of the AS_PATH exceeds the available writable space in the stream, causing a partial AS_PATH to be written and potentially causing a session drop. This can be exploited by an attacker to cause a denial-of-service condition.
